<div class="pageContent" id="pageContent">

<div class="headings">
<h1 class="pageHeader">Tibetan Buddhism Portal</h1>
</div>

<div class="row cat-detail justify-content-center">

<div class="col-12 col-sm-2 img">
<img src="/uploads/a/Tibetan-Buddhism-tall-2.jpg" class="img-fluid img-thumbnail" alt="category cover">
</div>
<div class="col-12 col-sm">

<p>Tibetan Buddhism includes schools such as Nyingma, Kadampa, Kagyu and Gelug. Their primary canon of literature is divided in two broad categories: The Kangyur, which consists of Buddha’s words, and the Tengyur, which includes commentaries from various sources. Esotericism and tantra techniques (<em>vajrayāna</em>) are collected indepently.</p>

<strong>Portal</strong>
&middot; <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/articles" title="Various tibetan-buddhism articles">Articles</a>
&middot; <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/updates" title="Latest tibetan-buddhism updates">Updates</a>
<!-- &middot;<a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary">Glossary</a> -->
<br>

<div class="cat-glossary mt-3">

<span>Glossary:</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/a">A</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/b">B</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/c">C</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/d">D</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/e">E</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/f">F</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/g">G</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/h">H</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/i">I</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/j">J</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/k">K</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/l">L</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/m">M</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/n">N</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/o">O</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/p">P</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/q">Q</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/r">R</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/s">S</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/t">T</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/u">U</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/v">V</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/w">W</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/x">X</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/y">Y</a> - <a href="/tibetan-buddhism/glossary/z">Z</a>	
</div>
